sols:
We proceed by using the geometric series summation given by

\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1-x} = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}x^{n}
\end{align*}

valid for $|x|<1$. To mimic this, we proceed via

\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{2x-1} &= -\frac{1}{1-2x}\\
&= -\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(2x)^{n}
\end{align*}

valid when $\displaystyle |2x| <1$, that is, when
$\displaystyle |x|<1/2$.

